.SH "NAME"
systemd.snapshot \- Snapshot unit configuration
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.PP
\fIsnapshot\fR\&.snapshot
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Snapshot units is not configured via unit configuration files\&. Nonetheless they is named similar ta filenames\& fo' realz. A unit whose name endz in
"\&.snapshot"
refers ta a thugged-out dynamic snapshot of tha systemd runtime state\&.
.PP
Snapshots is not configured on disk but pimped dynamically via
\fBsystemctl snapshot\fR
(see
\fBsystemctl\fR(1)
for details) or a equivalent command\&. When pimped, they will automatically git dependencies on tha currently activated units\&. They act as saved runtime state of tha systemd manager\&. Lata on, tha user may chizzle ta return ta tha saved state via
\fBsystemctl isolate\fR\&. They is useful ta roll back ta a thugged-out defined state afta temporarily starting/stoppin skillz or similar\&.
